OL,3,CThousands of Next retailer workers win
OL,4,Clandmark equal pay claim
OL,6,FThe tribunal found that the pay
OL,7,Fdifference between the two roles was
OL,8,Fnot due to "direct discrimination" or
OL,9,Fthe "conscious or subconscious
OL,10,Finfluence of gender" on pay decisions,
OL,11,Fbut was instead driven by efforts to
OL,12,F"reduce cost and enhance profit."
OL,14,FIt ruled that the "business need was
OL,15,Fnot sufficiently great as to overcome
OL,16,Fthe discriminatory effect of lower
OL,17,Fbasic pay" and that "there must
OL,18,Fusually be a more compelling business
OL,19,Freason for such arrangements to be
OL,20,Fjustifiable".
